  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The first term is the negative expected log-likelihood, i.e., the reconstruction error, where p Φ (x|) denotes the generation probability of x.",
    "As we sample words from the multinomial distribution, the first term becomes -x ⊤ log(f Φ).",
    "The second term is the Kullback-Lei- bler (KL) divergence between the variational and prior distributions, which can be computed through an analytical form (Srivastava and Sutton 2017).",
    "It is also known as a regularization term.",
    "The above is the fundamental structure of a VAE-based NTM."
  ],
